                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Fol. 1a. Arganon. The text is in the main identical with the other known manuscripts of the Arganon, for instance Ms. 97 of Zotenberg's Catalogue. It is divided into seven parts: 1a. for Monday -- 16a. Tuesday -- 30a. Wednesday -- 44a. Thursday -- 58a. Friday -- 70a.- Saturday -- 76a. Sunday -- 82a. An invocation to the Virgin. Attached to the Manuscript is a primitive aquarelle of the Virgin with Jesus in her arms. In the two upper corners, the Angels Michael and Gabriel.
                            . Cp. <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFet97">Paris, Bibliothèque nationale de France, BnF Éthiopien 97</ref>
                            
                        </summary>

                        
                    </msContents>
